# Templated for the org. Replace @<org>/quality-platform with real handles
# during onboarding. CODEOWNERS is enforced by GitHub branch-protection rules.

# CODEOWNERS — assigns review responsibility per area.
# Lines are matched bottom-up; the LAST matching pattern wins. See
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Replace @<org>/quality-platform with org / team handles when this lands in a
# multi-engineer org (e.g. @org/quality-platform).

# --- defaults --------------------------------------------------------------
*                                       @<org>/quality-platform

# --- per-phase ownership ---------------------------------------------------
/phase-1-ai-testing/                    @<org>/quality-platform
/phase-2-contract-testing/              @<org>/quality-platform
/phase-3-performance/                   @<org>/quality-platform
/phase-4-pipeline/                      @<org>/quality-platform

# --- platform / CI -- changes here block a deploy, so review bar is higher --
/.github/workflows/                     @<org>/quality-platform
/.github/CODEOWNERS                     @<org>/quality-platform
/docker-compose.yml                     @<org>/quality-platform
/Dockerfile                             @<org>/quality-platform
/phase-*/Dockerfile                     @<org>/quality-platform

# --- security / supply chain ------------------------------------------------
/.github/zap/                           @<org>/quality-platform
/SECURITY.md                            @<org>/quality-platform

# --- documentation ----------------------------------------------------------
/docs/adr/                              @<org>/quality-platform
/README.md                              @<org>/quality-platform
